{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hear us, Shepherd of Israel, you who lead Joseph like a flock,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "you who sit above the cherubim, shine out."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Before Ephraim, Benjamin, and Manasseh, stir up your might! Come to save us!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Turn us again, God. Cause your face to shine,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and we will be saved."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh God of Armies, how long will you be angry against the prayer of your people?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have fed them with the bread of tears, and given them tears to drink in large measure."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You make us a source of contention to our neighbors. Our enemies laugh among themselves."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Turn us again, God of Armies. Cause your face to shine,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and we will be saved."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You brought a vine out of Egypt. You drove out the nations, and planted it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You cleared the ground for it. It took deep root, and filled the land."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The mountains were covered with its shadow. Its boughs were like God’s cedars."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It sent out its branches to the sea, its shoots to the River."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Why have you broken down its walls, so that all those who pass by the way pluck it?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The boar out of the wood ravages it. The wild animals of the field feed on it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Turn again, we beg you, God of Armies. Look down from heaven, and see, and visit this vine,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "the stock which your right hand planted, the branch that you made strong for yourself."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It’s burned with fire. It’s cut down."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They perish at your rebuke."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let your hand be on the man of your right hand, on the son of man whom you made strong for yourself."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "So we will not turn away from you. Revive us, and we will call on your name."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Turn us again, Yahweh God of Armies. Cause your face to shine, and we will be saved."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}